  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "minor",
    "intended": "Let $Y(x)$ be the maximal $y$ such that there exists a choice of congruence classes $a_p$ for all primes $p\\leq x$ such that every integer in $[1,y]$ is congruent to at least one of the $a_p\\pmod{p}$. \n\nGive good estimates for $Y(x)$. In particular, can one prove that $Y(x)=o(x^2)$ or even $Y(x)\\ll x^{1+o(1)}$?",
